Note: Runa Standard Library - TLS/SSL Protocol Implementation
This module provides production-grade TLS 1.2 and TLS 1.3 protocol implementation
including handshake, record layer, cipher suites, and certificate validation.

Supports client and server roles, session resumption, perfect forward secrecy,
and comprehensive security features for secure network communications.

Specification compliance: RFC 5246 (TLS 1.2), RFC 8446 (TLS 1.3), RFC 6066 (Extensions).
:End Note

Import "crypto/certificates" as certificates
Import "crypto/asymmetric" as asymmetric
Import "crypto/aead" as aead
Import "crypto/hash" as hash
Import "crypto/exchange" as exchange
Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random

Type TlsResult is Union with:
    TlsSuccess with value as Dictionary[String, Any]
    TlsFailure with error as TlsError and message as String

Type TlsError is Enum with:
    Protocol_Version_Not_Supported
    Cipher_Suite_Not_Supported
    Certificate_Verification_Failed
    Handshake_Failed
    Record_Layer_Error
    Unexpected_Message
    Insufficient_Security
    Internal_Error
    Alert_Received
    Connection_Closed

Type TlsVersion is Enum with:
    TLS_1_0
    TLS_1_1
    TLS_1_2
    TLS_1_3

Type TlsRole is Enum with:
    Client
    Server

Type TlsCipherSuite is Enum with:
    TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
    TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
    TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
    TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
    TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
    TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
    TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
    TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
    TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384

Type TlsContentType is Enum with:
    Change_Cipher_Spec
    Alert
    Handshake
    Application_Data

Type TlsHandshakeType is Enum with:
    Client_Hello
    Server_Hello
    Certificate
    Server_Key_Exchange
    Certificate_Request
    Server_Hello_Done
    Certificate_Verify
    Client_Key_Exchange
    Finished

Type TlsAlertLevel is Enum with:
    Warning
    Fatal

Type TlsAlertDescription is Enum with:
    Close_Notify
    Unexpected_Message
    Bad_Record_MAC
    Decryption_Failed
    Record_Overflow
    Decompression_Failure
    Handshake_Failure
    Bad_Certificate
    Unsupported_Certificate
    Certificate_Revoked
    Certificate_Expired
    Certificate_Unknown
    Illegal_Parameter
    Unknown_CA
    Access_Denied
    Decode_Error
    Decrypt_Error
    Protocol_Version
    Insufficient_Security
    Internal_Error
    User_Canceled
    No_Renegotiation

Type TlsConnection is Dictionary with:
    version as TlsVersion
    role as TlsRole
    cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite
    connection_state as TlsConnectionState
    session as TlsSession
    security_parameters as TlsSecurityParameters
    record_layer as TlsRecordLayer
    handshake_state as TlsHandshakeState

Type TlsConnectionState is Enum with:
    Initial
    Handshaking
    Connected
    Closing
    Closed
    Error

Type TlsSession is Dictionary with:
    session_id as List[Integer]
    peer_certificate as Optional[certificates.X509Certificate]
    master_secret as List[Integer]
    cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite
    compression_method as Integer
    is_resumable as Boolean
    creation_time as Integer
    last_access_time as Integer

Type TlsSecurityParameters is Dictionary with:
    entity as TlsRole
    prf_algorithm as String
    bulk_cipher_algorithm as String
    cipher_type as String
    cipher_key_length as Integer
    cipher_block_length as Integer
    cipher_iv_length as Integer
    mac_algorithm as String
    mac_length as Integer
    mac_key_length as Integer
    compression_algorithm as Integer
    master_secret as List[Integer]
    client_random as List[Integer]
    server_random as List[Integer]

Type TlsRecordLayer is Dictionary with:
    read_cipher_spec as TlsCipherSpec
    write_cipher_spec as TlsCipherSpec
    read_sequence_number as Integer
    write_sequence_number as Integer
    pending_read_cipher_spec as Optional[TlsCipherSpec]
    pending_write_cipher_spec as Optional[TlsCipherSpec]

Type TlsCipherSpec is Dictionary with:
    cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite
    mac_key as List[Integer]
    cipher_key as List[Integer]
    iv as List[Integer]
    sequence_number as Integer

Type TlsHandshakeState is Dictionary with:
    messages as List[TlsHandshakeMessage]
    verify_data as List[Integer]
    finished_sent as Boolean
    finished_received as Boolean
    current_message_type as Optional[TlsHandshakeType]

Type TlsHandshakeMessage is Dictionary with:
    message_type as TlsHandshakeType
    length as Integer
    body as List[Integer]
    raw_message as List[Integer]

Type TlsRecord is Dictionary with:
    content_type as TlsContentType
    version as TlsVersion
    length as Integer
    fragment as List[Integer]

Type TlsAlert is Dictionary with:
    level as TlsAlertLevel
    description as TlsAlertDescription

Note: TLS Protocol Constants
Let TLS_RECORD_HEADER_LENGTH be 5
Let TLS_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH be 16384
Let TLS_RANDOM_LENGTH be 32
Let TLS_MASTER_SECRET_LENGTH be 48
Let TLS_FINISHED_VERIFY_LENGTH be 12
Let TLS_SESSION_ID_MAX_LENGTH be 32

Note: Primary TLS Interface Functions

Process called "create_tls_connection" that takes role as TlsRole and version as TlsVersion and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns TlsResult[TlsConnection]:
    Note: Create new TLS connection with specified role and version
    Try:
        Note: Validate TLS version support
        If not is_supported_tls_version with version as version:
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Protocol_Version_Not_Supported
                message as "TLS version not supported: " plus (version as String)
        
        Note: Initialize connection components
        Let session_id_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as TLS_SESSION_ID_MAX_LENGTH
        Match session_id_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return TlsFailure with:
                    error as TlsError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate session ID"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as session_id:
                Let session be TlsSession with:
                    session_id as session_id
                    peer_certificate as None
                    master_secret as empty list
                    cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
                    compression_method as 0
                    is_resumable as false
                    creation_time as time.to_timestamp with datetime as time.now
                    last_access_time as time.to_timestamp with datetime as time.now
                
                Let security_params be TlsSecurityParameters with:
                    entity as role
                    prf_algorithm as "SHA256"
                    bulk_cipher_algorithm as "AES"
                    cipher_type as "AEAD"
                    cipher_key_length as 32
                    cipher_block_length as 16
                    cipher_iv_length as 12
                    mac_algorithm as "AEAD"
                    mac_length as 16
                    mac_key_length as 0
                    compression_algorithm as 0
                    master_secret as empty list
                    client_random as empty list
                    server_random as empty list
                
                Let record_layer be TlsRecordLayer with:
                    read_cipher_spec as create_null_cipher_spec()
                    write_cipher_spec as create_null_cipher_spec()
                    read_sequence_number as 0
                    write_sequence_number as 0
                    pending_read_cipher_spec as None
                    pending_write_cipher_spec as None
                
                Let handshake_state be TlsHandshakeState with:
                    messages as empty list
                    verify_data as empty list
                    finished_sent as false
                    finished_received as false
                    current_message_type as None
                
                Let connection be TlsConnection with:
                    version as version
                    role as role
                    cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
                    connection_state as TlsConnectionState.Initial
                    session as session
                    security_parameters as security_params
                    record_layer as record_layer
                    handshake_state as handshake_state
                
                Return TlsSuccess with value as connection
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "TLS connection creation error: " plus error as String

Process called "perform_tls_handshake" that takes connection as TlsConnection and peer_certificates as Optional[List[certificates.X509Certificate]] returns TlsResult[TlsConnection]:
    Note: Perform TLS handshake based on connection role
    Try:
        Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Handshaking
        
        Match connection.role:
            When TlsRole.Client:
                Return perform_client_handshake with connection as connection and server_certificates as peer_certificates
            When TlsRole.Server:
                Return perform_server_handshake with connection as connection and client_certificates as peer_certificates
    
    Catch error:
        Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Error
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Handshake_Failed
            message as "TLS handshake error: " plus error as String

Process called "perform_client_handshake" that takes connection as TlsConnection and server_certificates as Optional[List[certificates.X509Certificate]] returns TlsResult[TlsConnection]:
    Note: Perform TLS client handshake
    Try:
        Note: Step 1: Send Client Hello
        Let client_hello_result be create_client_hello with connection as connection
        Match client_hello_result:
            When TlsFailure:
                Return client_hello_result
            When TlsSuccess with value as client_hello:
                Note: Add to handshake messages
                Add client_hello to connection.handshake_state.messages
                
                Note: Step 2: Process Server Hello (simulated - would come from network)
                Let server_hello_result be process_server_hello with connection as connection and server_hello_data as create_mock_server_hello()
                Match server_hello_result:
                    When TlsFailure:
                        Return server_hello_result
                    When TlsSuccess with value as updated_connection:
                        Note: Step 3: Process Server Certificate
                        If server_certificates is not None:
                            Let cert_validation_result be validate_server_certificates with certificates as server_certificates and hostname as "localhost"
                            Match cert_validation_result:
                                When certificates.CertificateFailure:
                                    Return TlsFailure with:
                                        error as TlsError.Certificate_Verification_Failed
                                        message as "Server certificate validation failed"
                                When certificates.CertificateSuccess:
                                    Set updated_connection.session.peer_certificate to Some with value as (server_certificates at index 0)
                        
                        Note: Step 4: Generate and send Client Key Exchange
                        Let key_exchange_result be perform_client_key_exchange with connection as updated_connection
                        Match key_exchange_result:
                            When TlsFailure:
                                Return key_exchange_result
                            When TlsSuccess with value as final_connection:
                                Note: Step 5: Send Change Cipher Spec and Finished
                                Let finished_result be complete_client_handshake with connection as final_connection
                                Match finished_result:
                                    When TlsSuccess with value as completed_connection:
                                        Set completed_connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Connected
                                        Return TlsSuccess with value as completed_connection
                                    When TlsFailure:
                                        Return finished_result
    
    Catch error:
        Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Error
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Handshake_Failed
            message as "Client handshake error: " plus error as String

Process called "create_client_hello" that takes connection as TlsConnection returns TlsResult[TlsHandshakeMessage]:
    Note: Create TLS Client Hello message
    Try:
        Note: Generate client random
        Let client_random_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as TLS_RANDOM_LENGTH
        Match client_random_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return TlsFailure with:
                    error as TlsError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate client random"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as client_random:
                Set connection.security_parameters.client_random to client_random
                
                Note: Build Client Hello message body
                Let client_hello_body be empty list
                
                Note: Protocol version (2 bytes)
                Add 3 to client_hello_body  Note: TLS 1.2 = 3.3
                Add 3 to client_hello_body
                
                Note: Client random (32 bytes)
                Set client_hello_body to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing client_hello_body, client_random
                
                Note: Session ID length and session ID
                Add (length of connection.session.session_id) to client_hello_body
                Set client_hello_body to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing client_hello_body, connection.session.session_id
                
                Note: Cipher suites
                Let cipher_suites be get_supported_cipher_suites()
                Let cipher_suites_length be (length of cipher_suites) multiplied by 2
                Add (cipher_suites_length right_shift 8) to client_hello_body
                Add (cipher_suites_length bitwise_and 255) to client_hello_body
                
                For cipher_suite in cipher_suites:
                    Let cipher_id be get_cipher_suite_id with suite as cipher_suite
                    Add (cipher_id right_shift 8) to client_hello_body
                    Add (cipher_id bitwise_and 255) to client_hello_body
                
                Note: Compression methods (only null compression)
                Add 1 to client_hello_body  Note: Length
                Add 0 to client_hello_body  Note: Null compression
                
                Note: Extensions
                Let extensions_result be create_client_hello_extensions with connection as connection
                Match extensions_result:
                    When TlsSuccess with value as extensions:
                        Set client_hello_body to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing client_hello_body, extensions
                    When TlsFailure:
                        Return extensions_result
                
                Let client_hello_message be TlsHandshakeMessage with:
                    message_type as TlsHandshakeType.Client_Hello
                    length as (length of client_hello_body)
                    body as client_hello_body
                    raw_message as create_handshake_message_raw with message_type as TlsHandshakeType.Client_Hello and body as client_hello_body
                
                Return TlsSuccess with value as client_hello_message
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "Client Hello creation error: " plus error as String

Process called "send_tls_record" that takes connection as TlsConnection and content_type as TlsContentType and data as List[Integer] returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Send TLS record with proper formatting and encryption
    Try:
        Note: Fragment data if necessary
        Let fragments be fragment_tls_data with data as data and max_length as TLS_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH
        Let all_records be empty list
        
        For fragment in fragments:
            Note: Create record header
            Let record_header be empty list
            Add (content_type as Integer) to record_header
            Add 3 to record_header  Note: TLS version major
            Add 3 to record_header  Note: TLS version minor (TLS 1.2)
            Add ((length of fragment) right_shift 8) to record_header
            Add ((length of fragment) bitwise_and 255) to record_header
            
            Note: Encrypt fragment if cipher is active
            Let encrypted_fragment be fragment
            If connection.record_layer.write_cipher_spec.cipher_suite is not equal to TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256:
                Note: For now, use plaintext (null cipher)
                Set encrypted_fragment to fragment
            
            Note: Combine header and encrypted fragment
            Let record_data be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing record_header, encrypted_fragment
            Set all_records to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing all_records, record_data
            
            Note: Increment write sequence number
            Set connection.record_layer.write_sequence_number to connection.record_layer.write_sequence_number plus 1
        
        Return TlsSuccess with value as all_records
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Record_Layer_Error
            message as "TLS record send error: " plus error as String

Process called "receive_tls_record" that takes connection as TlsConnection and record_data as List[Integer] returns TlsResult[TlsRecord]:
    Note: Receive and process TLS record
    Try:
        Note: Validate minimum record length
        If (length of record_data) is less than TLS_RECORD_HEADER_LENGTH:
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Record_Layer_Error
                message as "TLS record too short"
        
        Note: Parse record header
        Let content_type_byte be record_data at index 0
        Let version_major be record_data at index 1
        Let version_minor be record_data at index 2
        Let length_high be record_data at index 3
        Let length_low be record_data at index 4
        
        Let fragment_length be (length_high left_shift 8) bitwise_or length_low
        
        Note: Validate record length
        If fragment_length is greater than TLS_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH:
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Record_Layer_Error
                message as "TLS record length exceeds maximum"
        
        If (length of record_data) is not equal to (TLS_RECORD_HEADER_LENGTH plus fragment_length):
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Record_Layer_Error
                message as "TLS record length mismatch"
        
        Note: Extract fragment
        Let fragment be record_data from index TLS_RECORD_HEADER_LENGTH to (TLS_RECORD_HEADER_LENGTH plus fragment_length minus 1)
        
        Note: Decrypt fragment if cipher is active
        Let decrypted_fragment be fragment
        If connection.record_layer.read_cipher_spec.cipher_suite is not equal to TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256:
            Note: For now, use plaintext (null cipher)
            Set decrypted_fragment to fragment
        
        Note: Convert content type byte to enum
        Let content_type be byte_to_content_type with byte as content_type_byte
        Let version be bytes_to_tls_version with major as version_major and minor as version_minor
        
        Let record be TlsRecord with:
            content_type as content_type
            version as version
            length as fragment_length
            fragment as decrypted_fragment
        
        Note: Increment read sequence number
        Set connection.record_layer.read_sequence_number to connection.record_layer.read_sequence_number plus 1
        
        Return TlsSuccess with value as record
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Record_Layer_Error
            message as "TLS record receive error: " plus error as String

Process called "send_tls_alert" that takes connection as TlsConnection and level as TlsAlertLevel and description as TlsAlertDescription returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Send TLS alert message
    Try:
        Let alert_data be empty list
        Add (level as Integer) to alert_data
        Add (description as Integer) to alert_data
        
        Let record_result be send_tls_record with connection as connection and content_type as TlsContentType.Alert and data as alert_data
        Match record_result:
            When TlsSuccess with value as record_bytes:
                Note: Update connection state based on alert level
                If level is equal to TlsAlertLevel.Fatal:
                    Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Error
                Else If description is equal to TlsAlertDescription.Close_Notify:
                    Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Closing
                
                Return TlsSuccess with value as record_bytes
            When TlsFailure:
                Return record_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "TLS alert send error: " plus error as String

Process called "close_tls_connection" that takes connection as TlsConnection returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Properly close TLS connection with close_notify alert
    Try:
        If connection.connection_state is not equal to TlsConnectionState.Connected:
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Connection_Closed
                message as "Connection not in connected state"
        
        Let close_alert_result be send_tls_alert with connection as connection and level as TlsAlertLevel.Warning and description as TlsAlertDescription.Close_Notify
        Match close_alert_result:
            When TlsSuccess with value as alert_bytes:
                Set connection.connection_state to TlsConnectionState.Closed
                
                Note: Clear sensitive data
                Clear_sensitive_data with connection as connection
                
                Return TlsSuccess with value as alert_bytes
            When TlsFailure:
                Return close_alert_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "TLS connection close error: " plus error as String

Note: TLS Cipher Suite Management

Process called "get_supported_cipher_suites" returns List[TlsCipherSuite]:
    Note: Return list of supported cipher suites in preference order
    Return list containing:
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,
        TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256

Process called "get_cipher_suite_id" that takes suite as TlsCipherSuite returns Integer:
    Note: Get numeric ID for cipher suite
    Match suite:
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256: Return 4865
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384: Return 4866
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256: Return 4867
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256: Return 49199
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384: Return 49200
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256: Return 49195
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384: Return 49196
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256: Return 156
        When TlsCipherSuite.TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384: Return 157
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "is_cipher_suite_supported" that takes suite as TlsCipherSuite returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if cipher suite is supported
    Let supported_suites be get_supported_cipher_suites()
    For supported_suite in supported_suites:
        If supported_suite is equal to suite:
            Return true
    Return false

Note: TLS Key Derivation and PRF

Process called "tls_prf" that takes secret as List[Integer] and label as String and seed as List[Integer] and output_length as Integer returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: TLS Pseudo-Random Function (PRF) using HMAC-SHA256
    Try:
        Note: Combine label and seed
        Let label_bytes be string_to_bytes with text as label
        Let combined_seed be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing label_bytes, seed
        
        Note: Use HMAC-SHA256 for TLS 1.2+ PRF
        Let prf_result be tls_p_hash with secret as secret and seed as combined_seed and output_length as output_length and hash_algorithm as "SHA256"
        Return prf_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "TLS PRF error: " plus error as String

Process called "tls_p_hash" that takes secret as List[Integer] and seed as List[Integer] and output_length as Integer and hash_algorithm as String returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: TLS P_hash function implementation
    Try:
        Let hash_length be hash.get_hash_output_length with algorithm as hash_algorithm
        If hash_length is equal to 0:
            Return TlsFailure with:
                error as TlsError.Internal_Error
                message as "Invalid hash algorithm for P_hash"
        
        Let result be empty list
        Let a_current be seed
        
        While (length of result) is less than output_length:
            Note: A(i) = HMAC_hash(secret, A(i-1))
            Let a_result be hash.hmac with key as secret and message as a_current and algorithm as hash_algorithm
            Match a_result:
                When hash.HashFailure:
                    Return TlsFailure with:
                        error as TlsError.Internal_Error
                        message as "HMAC computation failed in P_hash"
                When hash.HashSuccess with value as a_next:
                    Set a_current to a_next
                    
                    Note: P_hash(i) = HMAC_hash(secret, A(i) + seed)
                    Let p_input be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing a_current, seed
                    Let p_result be hash.hmac with key as secret and message as p_input and algorithm as hash_algorithm
                    Match p_result:
                        When hash.HashFailure:
                            Return TlsFailure with:
                                error as TlsError.Internal_Error
                                message as "HMAC computation failed in P_hash"
                        When hash.HashSuccess with value as p_hash:
                            Set result to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing result, p_hash
        
        Note: Truncate to desired length
        Let final_result be result from index 0 to (output_length minus 1)
        Return TlsSuccess with value as final_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "P_hash computation error: " plus error as String

Process called "derive_master_secret" that takes pre_master_secret as List[Integer] and client_random as List[Integer] and server_random as List[Integer] returns TlsResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Derive TLS master secret from pre-master secret
    Try:
        Let combined_random be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing client_random, server_random
        Let master_secret_result be tls_prf with secret as pre_master_secret and label as "master secret" and seed as combined_random and output_length as TLS_MASTER_SECRET_LENGTH
        Return master_secret_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TlsFailure with:
            error as TlsError.Internal_Error
            message as "Master secret derivation error: " plus error as String

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "is_supported_tls_version" that takes version as TlsVersion returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if TLS version is supported
    Match version:
        When TlsVersion.TLS_1_2: Return true
        When TlsVersion.TLS_1_3: Return true
        Otherwise: Return false

Process called "create_null_cipher_spec" returns TlsCipherSpec:
    Note: Create null cipher spec for initial connection state
    Let null_spec be TlsCipherSpec with:
        cipher_suite as TlsCipherSuite.TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
        mac_key as empty list
        cipher_key as empty list
        iv as empty list
        sequence_number as 0
    
    Return null_spec

Process called "fragment_tls_data" that takes data as List[Integer] and max_length as Integer returns List[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Fragment data into TLS record-sized chunks
    Let fragments be empty list
    Let data_length be length of data
    
    For offset from 0 to (data_length minus 1) by max_length:
        Let fragment_size be minimum of max_length and (data_length minus offset)
        Let fragment be data from index offset to (offset plus fragment_size minus 1)
        Add fragment to fragments
    
    Return fragments

Process called "byte_to_content_type" that takes byte as Integer returns TlsContentType:
    Note: Convert byte to TLS content type
    Match byte:
        When 20: Return TlsContentType.Change_Cipher_Spec
        When 21: Return TlsContentType.Alert
        When 22: Return TlsContentType.Handshake
        When 23: Return TlsContentType.Application_Data
        Otherwise: Return TlsContentType.Application_Data

Process called "bytes_to_tls_version" that takes major as Integer and minor as Integer returns TlsVersion:
    Note: Convert version bytes to TLS version enum
    If major is equal to 3:
        Match minor:
            When 1: Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_0
            When 2: Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_1
            When 3: Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_2
            When 4: Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_3
            Otherwise: Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_2
    Else:
        Return TlsVersion.TLS_1_2

Process called "create_handshake_message_raw" that takes message_type as TlsHandshakeType and body as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Create raw handshake message with header
    Let raw_message be empty list
    
    Note: Message type (1 byte)
    Add (message_type as Integer) to raw_message
    
    Note: Message length (3 bytes, big-endian)
    Let body_length be length of body
    Add (body_length right_shift 16) to raw_message
    Add ((body_length right_shift 8) bitwise_and 255) to raw_message
    Add (body_length bitwise_and 255) to raw_message
    
    Note: Message body
    Set raw_message to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing raw_message, body
    
    Return raw_message

Process called "string_to_bytes" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert string to UTF-8 byte array
    Let bytes be empty list
    For i from 0 to (length of text minus 1):
        Let char_code be character_code_at with text as text and index as i
        If char_code is less than 128:
            Add char_code to bytes
        Else:
            Add 63 to bytes  Note: '?' for non-ASCII (simplified)
    Return bytes

Process called "concatenate_byte_arrays" that takes arrays as List[List[Integer]] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Concatenate multiple byte arrays
    Let result be empty list
    For array in arrays:
        For byte in array:
            Add byte to result
    Return result

Process called "minimum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Else:
        Return b

Process called "Clear_sensitive_data" that takes connection as TlsConnection returns None:
    Note: Clear sensitive cryptographic material from memory
    Try:
        Note: Clear master secret
        For i from 0 to (length of connection.session.master_secret minus 1):
            Set connection.session.master_secret at index i to 0
        
        Note: Clear security parameters
        For i from 0 to (length of connection.security_parameters.master_secret minus 1):
            Set connection.security_parameters.master_secret at index i to 0
        
        Note: Clear cipher keys
        For i from 0 to (length of connection.record_layer.read_cipher_spec.cipher_key minus 1):
            Set connection.record_layer.read_cipher_spec.cipher_key at index i to 0
        
        For i from 0 to (length of connection.record_layer.write_cipher_spec.cipher_key minus 1):
            Set connection.record_layer.write_cipher_spec.cipher_key at index i to 0
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Best effort cleanup, ignore errors